oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Clown with Carnival Midway
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Clowns; Carnivals; Woodcuts (prints);
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Three color card fragment (blue, red, and yellow on white) featuring a woodcut of a clown pointing and a carnival scene. The poster was probably printed and designed by the Triangle Poster Printing Company, which is partially written on the back of the fragment.
